-- Flaherty Says He's Satisfied With Mandate of Bank of Canada on Inflation
-- B y   A l e x a n d r e   D e s l o n g c h a m p s
-- 2010-12-10T14:47:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/flaherty-says-he-s-satisfied-with-mandate-of-bank-of-canada-on-inflation.html
Canadian Finance Minister Jim
Flaherty said he’s satisfied with the mandate of the Bank of
Canada.  Flaherty was speaking in an interview on “Bloomberg
Surveillance” with Tom Keene. The central bank’s mandate is to
keep the inflation rate at 2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexandre Deslongchamps in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
